commit.message: fixes https://github.com/jorgenschaefer/elpy/issues/1937
Remove debug statement

fix test for empty output when displaying hook output buffer

Fixes #102

fix python executable used in pyvenv-run-virtualenvwrapper-hook

Hardcoded `python` was used to execute virtualenvwrapper module when
running hooks.

This can fail in pre_activate since the new virtualenv is not yet
activated: there's no guarantee that `python` exists in the system.

Using the configurable variable `pyvenv-virtualenvwrapper-python` is
more correct.

Note that this was happening before commit 74ab422 but that commit
made the problem evident to me since the process output parsing has
changed.

Ensure env vars are read from JSON as strings

`setenv` expects variables to be strings. If a user has `json-key-type` set to
something other than `'string`, the later call to `setenv` will fail.

Improve working with env variables

- restore affected variables one-by-one instead of restoring the entire
  `process-environment' list to its pre-activation state, to avoid losing
  unrelated env changes that were applied when the virtualenv was active

- when deactivating, only remove paths that were added during activation

- when tracking env changes from virtualenvwrapper hooks, calculate diff before
  and after the hook is run, to avoid fetching env-vars set by python or the
  shell itself

Use pyvenv-virtualenvwrapper-python for pyvenv-create

This re-uses the logic to finding the correct python interpreter
for create calls, too.
Support python3 by default
Mark unused arguments
Add new `pyvenv-default-virtual-env-name' customizable variable.
Bump version: 1.20 → 1.21
Fallback to 'venv' when 'virtualenv' is not installed
Bump version: 1.19 → 1.20
Reduced expression used to determine when to skip re-activation.
Removed trailing newline in docstring.

Always skip reactivation in pyvenv-workon.

This also removes the unnecessary check for whether pyvenv-virtual-env-name is
already bound.

Added support for avoiding reactivation of active environment.

You can now pass a flag to `pyvenv-workon` that tells it to do nothing if the
requested environment is already active.

Prefer bash over sh as a POSIX shell

Debian's ash does not support the source command etc.

Fixes #71

Fall back to shell-file-name for the POSIX shell

Not all systems do have a sh or bash. Say, like, Windows.

Fixes #70
New feature for virtual environments creation

Set the shell while running hooks with a customization variable (#69)

* Set the shell while running hooks with a customization variable

This commit defines a new customization var, `pyvenv-exec-shell`, the value of
which should be a POSIX-compliant shell binary. We then set this to be the value
of `shell-file-name` during hook loading. This allows those of us using
suchlikeas fish shell to have an error free activate/deactivate experience.

Closes #49

* PR feedback
